column2: "It kinda feels anticlimactic, given how easily we got in."
"Of course. For I am this star's Miko."
"Normally, the Kuron King would hang his headeth and cometh to mine own shrine."
"For him to submit a letter and me to maketh a personal visit... he's becometh quite conceited."
"Sukuna-hime, have you met the Kuron King?"
"Of course. 'long with both kings' enthronements I putteth up with their meetings."
"Though the Shironian King hadst an aptitude for techniques, I hath felt he wast a coward and hadst nay capacity as a king."
"As for the Kuron King, he was wise. I didn't quite enjoy his pride, but he was a cute little thing."
"You did raise the issue that the Kuronites were being manipulated by [Double] to the Kuron King, yes?"
"Yond's right. If the Kuronites maketh a moveth, through their rivalry, the Shironians will unilaterally moveth as well."
"Then, we shalt findeth those ominous children and exorcise them in one breath."
"This way, we avoid any more useless sacrifices."
"Fufu."
"What is it? What's so funny, Matoi?"
"I thought that no matter what Sukuna-hime says, she's really nice."
"You're always saying how the planet's important, but you also treasure the Kuronites and the Shironians as well, right?"
"Rather than treasure, it's more like thine own duty."
"Duty?"
"A duty yond been carved into thine own body since my birth."
"As the legends sayeth, I was born from a Kuronite father and Shironian mother, a child of ash. As such, both Shironians and Kuronites art mine own relatives."
"Black or white, I can oft leaveth their foolishness alone, but only a fiend would abandon their kin."
"As mine own father and mother did bless me with this life, I cannot doth yond."
"I'm sorry... I shouldn't have joked about that."
"Kaka, don't worry. Tis just banter to passeth the time. If't be true we wast serious, we would best in a lodging only I knoweth. "
"However, the desire to protect something or someone can produce power beyond the pale."
"Matoi, thee shouldst ponder what it is that yond the wanteth to protect."
"What, I want to protect..."
"It shouldn't be something as vague as \"everyone\", you know?"
